args:
Jinlorda blocks the way of the prince and his
allies as they make for the summit of the sacred
tree. With the atmosphere thick with tension,
the prince seeks to understand Nedrick's goals.
But Jinlorda replies with an attack, claiming he
will tell the prince only if he proves worthy.
At long last, we have reached the summit\nof the Sacred Tree, where the Dawnshard\nslumbers.
It contains a power great enough to alter\nfate itselfâ€”a power I intend to use for the\nsake of this world.
As custodian of the sacred shards, I would\nhear any objections you have now.
In accordance with Finlorda's request, \nwe followed Nedrick, Jinlorda, and Zethia\nto the Sacred Tree.
There's no telling what will happen if Nedrick\ngets his hands on the Dawnshard and forms a\npact with Bahamut.
We have to catch up to themâ€”both to protect\nthe Dawnshard and so we can finally discover\nNedrick's true aims!
Sacred Tree: Upper Strata\nAbove the Clouds
We've climbed and we've climbed,\nbut we've still got a ways to go.
I'm totally beat, you guys. Beat like a rug.
Sadly, we do not have the luxury of rest;\nNedrick and Jinlorda have likely made it\nto the summit already.
The place where the Dawnshard lies.
We need to catch him before he can claim\nthe shard. We must discover his true aim.
Finlorda said he was going to secure the\nDawnshard and make a new pact with\nBahamut, but that's not the whole story.
Yes, it tells us WHAT he's planning to do,\nbut we still have no idea as to the WHY.
You're right. His true goal is a mystery.
Which is why we must catch him.
Though whether or not he speaks the truth\nis another matter entirely.
It's obviously villainous papâ€”dominating\nthe world or some other hamfistery.
I must say I'm a bit insulted that you\nwould believe his motives are something\nso trifling.
It seems we rate a visit from the son of\nFinlorda. What an honor.
Do not compare me to the man who so\neasily surrendered the future of my people.
Likely at the summit of the tree. As for me,\nI chose to remain here and stop you.
I hope you are prepared to die.
Stop this, Jinlorda. We have no quarrel\nwith youâ€”let us pass in peace.
You may have no desire to fight, but we\nfaeries have plenty of reason to do so.
You are here because Finlorda told you\nto stop Nedrick, yes?
Yes. We gave him our word that we\nwould protect the Dawnshard.
I knew your body was a puppet wrought by\nFinlorda's hand, but it seems you are his\npuppet in mind as well.

You spare no thought for the right or wrong
of a thing, and merely carry out his orders
with feckless, blind obedience. You might
as well have strings upon your back.

With due respect, Your Majesty, what good
is it for us to know the right of a thing if
the situation is already past the point
of changing?
We need to know your plans. So you can\neither tell us now, or we can detain you\nand the information by different means.
Which is why I have no recourse\nbut violence.

Look, you're right in that there are many
things we don't know about why you're
taking these actions, but I want to know.
I want to understand you.
What is Nedrick trying to accomplish?\nWhat does he hope to gain by making a\npact with Bahamut?
We can't judge the right and wrong of your\nactions until we know those things.
Would it be possible for you to let go of\nthose emotions and cooperate with him?
I don't knowâ€”I honestly don't. But if I can\nbe convinced that what Nedrick is doing is\nright, I would be willing to help.
A model response! But words are wind that\ncan be formed into any shape we wish.
Then what would you have us do?
Our world is such that those without\nstrength lack agency of their own.
It is a bitter truth that both Nedrick and\nmyself have experienced far too often.
But seeing as that is the world we live in,\nwe will yield to itâ€”for now.
If force is all that matters in this world,\nthen I would put yours to the test.
If you can defeat me, I will tell you one\nof the answers you seek.
I was hoping it wouldn't come to this,\nbut it seems we have no choice!
